added.title: Teen Titans Vroom
added.description: Teen Titans Vroom: Part 1: In this episode of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans gain the ability to transform into cars. /Teen Titans Vroom: Part 2: In the exciting conclusion of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans must learn to work together to stop Dr. Military.

added.title: Bucket List
added.description: The Titans give Starfire a bucket list of activities to accomplish.

added.title: Cartoon Feud
added.description: Control Freak forces the Titans and the Scooby Gang to compete on Family Feud.

added.title: The One
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are joking around, but when Tobias joins in and makes fun of Gumball, he's incredibly offended. They explain to Tobias that to make those jokes he'd need to be higher on Gumball's friend list. They think that's the end of it, but Tobias is after that number one spot.

added.title: The Faith
added.description: Everything in Elmore is suddenly just various shades of grey, and things all over town are going wrong. Gumball and Darwin follow the mayhem and learn that one person was holding the whole town together: Alan. They have to restore his faith in the world to bring color back to Elmore.

added.title: The Schooling
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are at the convenience store considering playing truant. Larry warns them that if they don't take their education seriously they'll end up like him. To prove his point, Larry lets Gumball and Darwin work some of his many roles to make them appreciate the value of a good education.

added.title: The Buddy
added.description: Anais and school psycho Jamie are accused of the same techno-crime. They are forced to team up to discover the real culprit in order to prove their innocence. After solving the case, they realize that they have more in common than they thought...

added.title: The Master
added.description: Dad decides to resolve the Watterson family's differences through the power and magic of his favorite roleplaying game. As they embark on the adventure of a lifetime and battle mythical creatures, will they finally manage to put their differences aside and work together?

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Under the Overpass
added.description: Craig and his friends travel to find honeysuckle in the creek but discover a whole new part of the creek.

added.title: The Invitation
added.description: Craig and his friends are invited to an exclusive tea party with delicious desserts, if they can last to the end of the party.

added.title: Vulture's Nest
added.description: Craig and his friends start a band, but Craig is haunted by a frightening nightmare.

added.title: Royal Flush
added.description: When the other kids fear Harold has accidentally flushed himself down Chef's fancy new toilet, they travel into the sewer on a rescue mission. But will they find Harold before the mythical Alligator King traps them underground forever?

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Fart
added.description: After accidentally swallowing her first loose tooth and fearing that means no cash under the pillow, Leshawna tries to capture the tooth fairy. Instead, she accidentally captures the fart fairy. This comes with great consequence.

added.title: Dissing Cousins
added.description: It's International Cousins Day and Owen and Gwen are dreading the fact that their cousins Max and Ella are spending the day with them. And soon everyone else will understand why.

added.title: For a Few Duncans More
added.description: While trying to photocopy his butt on Chef's fancy new copier Duncan accidentally makes an entire other Duncan. Great! This other Duncan can do all the school stuff while the real Duncan chills. But things go badly when the other Duncan decides to copy himself so he can chill too.

added.title: He Who Wears the Clown
added.description: After trying on the nose of a clown Owen learns that this is how clowns are made and he is stuck as a clown until he can trick someone else into asking to try on the nose.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Ranger Tabes
added.description: To recover a missing package, the Bears get help from Ranger Tabes, an eccentric forest ranger. But her overblown sense of justice might be too much for the Bears to handle.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Cellie
added.description: Fed up with sharing, Panda forbids his brothers from using his cellphone any longer. But when the brothers get their own super advanced smartphones, Panda starts to succumb to crippling jealousy.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: Follow Your Dreams
added.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Onion must stop Apple from falling prey to his obsession, but a certain phone game is proving to be quite an obstacle.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion are faced with a philosophical question: Are they truly doing good deeds for the good of other people or is it all just for them?

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a formula for comedy that will land him a movie role.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

added.title: Super-Villain Team-Up
added.description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

added.title: Can I Keep It?
added.description: After stumbling upon a cute cat-dog-rabbit creature hybrid, or "Cadobbit," Ben ignores Grandpa Max's advice and sneaks the animal onto the Rustbucket, but is quickly in over his head as Dr. Amino's creation turns on him!

added.title: Chicken Nuggets of Wisdom
added.description: When Ben and Max get into an argument, Ben goes Heatblast to blow off steam against Max's wishes; but once Dr. Animo spots him and subsequently turns Max into a chicken, it's up to Ben to right his wrong if he is to save his Grandpa and stop Dr. Animo.

added.title: All Koiled Up
added.description: When Ben grows impatient with the snail like pace of gardening, he goes O-E Overflow to pick up the pace and accidentally floods the community garden, but once a giant sink hole appears and frees King Koil and his Kimodo Dragon from below, Ben must quickly right his wrong and capture the baddies if he is to save the coastal city of Bayburgh.

added.title: King Koil
added.description: Ben and Gwen spend the day volunteering at Repto Ranch and come face to face with King Koil, but need to quickly overcome their fear of snakes if they are to rescue the released critters and defeat the slithery baddie.

added.title: #MisgivingTree
added.description: Jessica Cruz and Pam Isley bond over protecting an ancient tree from being cut down. Neither of them realizes who the other's alter ego is, or the lengths to which they'll go to protect what's important.

added.title: #IllusionsOfGrandeur
added.description: Ready to emerge from her father's shadow, Zee Zatara secretly seeks fame and acclaim performing for her own audience at the pier. But when her act is dismissed as fakery, she loses her cool and accidentally unleashes mischievous gremlins who run wild all over the pier.

added.title: #BeastsInShow
added.description: When Babs and Kara spar over whose dog is better, they decide to settle it at the Metropolis Dog Show, where Ace the Bat-Hound and Krypto the Superdog suddenly find themselves called upon to save the day… in more ways than one.

added.title: #GothamCon
added.description: A fun day for Barbara Gordon and her bestie Harleen Quinzel (at Gotham City's annual geekfest, the Annual Convention of Gotham City Enthusiats!) is turned on its head when, out of nowhere, the villainous Harley Quinn shows up to wreak havoc! Lucky for everyone, Batgirl just happens to be in the area...

added.title: #Abracadabrapalooza
added.description: In an attempt to make Karen feel better about a pimple, Zee recounts her embarrassing transition into magichood, and the rift it created between her and her father.

added.title: Developing Dilemna
added.description: Frankie lets Elliott get a pet, which doesn't go down well with their new neighbor.

added.title: Inadvertant Inversion
added.description: As Elliott, Mo and Frankie all try something new at the Hive, they find their worlds are about to be turned upside down again.

added.title: Restaurant Wars
added.description: Steven must help the Frymans and the Pizzas settle a reignited rivalry between their restaurants.

added.title: Kiki's Pizza Delivery Service
added.description: Steven saves Kiki from some delicious nightmares.

added.title: Monster Reunion
added.description: Steven reunites with an old friend.

added.title: Alone at Sea
added.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

added.title: Greg the Babysitter
added.description: Steven learns the tale of how Greg came to work at the car wash.

added.title: Professor Proofed
added.description: After the Professor's latest experiment goes awry, the girls become overprotective.

added.title: Poorbucks
added.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

added.title: Snow Month
added.description: After a snow day saves Blossom from having to face a boy who's asked her out, she decides to use her ice breath to keep it going even if that means plunging Townsville into eternal winter complete with monstrous yetis!

added.title: Somewhere Over the Swingset
added.description: When the girls disobey the Professor and swing all the way over the swing set, they must deal with unexpected consequences.

added.title: People Pleaser
added.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

added.title: The Wild Hunt
added.description: A fierce creature is terrorizing the Candy Kingdom but before Finn can slay the beast, he must first overcome a guilty conscience.

added.title: Son of Rap Bear
added.description: When Flame Princess is coaxed into a high stakes battle against the indomitable Son of Rap Bear, Finn must help her search for a new strategy.

added.title: Seventeen
added.description: A mysterious knight crashes Finn's birthday bash and presents him with a dangerous gift.

added.title: Blenanas
added.description: Finn's latest literary work is met with only derision so he sets out to prove all the naysayers wrong.

added.title: The Ultimate Adventure: Come Along with Me
added.description: The fate of Ooo is revealed to two adventurers in the distant future. Princess Bubblegum gathers her allies while Finn searches for a way to prevent the coming Great Gum War.

added.title: ThunderDogs
added.description: The Thundercats agree to foster a demonic puppy from the Astral Plane until they can find it the perfect owner. But could the perfect owner be their worst enemy? Their worst enemy is Mumm-Ra in case you forgot!

added.title: Mini Mongor
added.description: The Thunderkittens unleash a demon who is powered by fear. Too bad he's small and not that scary.

added.title: Swampy Johnny
added.description: The Thundercats invite a super cool swamp man into the Cat's Lair who is on the run from some scary looking aliens!

added.title: Tygra's Garden
added.description: Tygra says he's done being a Thundercat after he gets engaged to a sentient flower. Now it's up to Lion-O to break up the wedding!

added.title: The Space Beam
added.description: The new rulers of Plun-Darr say they'll bring one of the Mutants home; whichever one of them activates a homing beacon that will blow up the Thundercats. Now it's every Mutant for themselves as they battle it out to be the one to activate the beacon!

added.title: The Never-Realm
added.description: The ninja arrive in the Never-Realm where they quickly find themselves overwhelmed. Luckily, they are taken in by a tribe of Ice Fishers who tell them Zane has been imprisoned by the evil Ice Emperor.

added.title: Fire Maker
added.description: The Ice Emperor learns of the ninja's arrival and sends his Blizzard Samurai warriors to destroy them and the villagers who sheltered them.

added.title: An Unlikely Ally
added.description: Lloyd runs afoul of the Ice Emperor's Blizzard Samurai but is rescued by a strange wolf with whom an unlikely friendship develops.

added.title: The Absolute Worst!
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, three criminals learn of the ninja's absence and stage a breakout of Kryptarium Prison, telling tall tales of how they were captured as they go.

added.title: The Message
added.description: Lloyd and his wolf-companion find a cave with the mech inside and a message from Zane that provides a clue to his fate.

added.title: Cool Guy Clarence
added.description: When Clarence meets JT, the kid who mows their lawn, he finds a fast friend who shows him some cool new music, a new outlook on life and a sweet rat-tail! Clarence leans into the rat tail lifestyle, discovering a whole new side of Aberdale he never knew existed.

added.title: Just Wait in the Car
added.description: As Mary runs errands, Clarence waits in the car and struggles to fight boredom.

added.title: Missing Cat
added.description: When Chelsea accidentally lets her pet cat Crumbles out, the cat goes missing! Reluctant to ask for help, she struggles to find the cat before anyone realizes it's gone. It's up to cat whisperer Clarence to interject and find Crumbles, whether Chelsea wants his help or not!

added.title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
added.description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

added.title: Dare Day
added.description: With Jeff on vacation, Sumo and Clarence egg each other on in a series of increasingly absurd and extreme dares. But will one of them put a stop to this dare day, before it goes too far?

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: New Bro on Campus
added.description: High School Muscle Man wants to prove he's cooler than the new kid on campus.

added.title: Daddy Issues
added.description: C.J. wants to win a "cut the Cheeser's" card at a mini-golf tournament.

added.title: The End of Muscle Man
added.description: The guys want to help Muscle Man finish his bucket list.

added.title: Lift With Your Back
added.description: Rigby wants to prove to Mordecai that he can earn a paycheck from another job.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: Green with Envy
added.description: When the local news interviews Uncle Andrew about his toy inventing, an envious Galileo stages a play in the park with the help of Axel and the team, only to be interrupted by an equally envious Madcap - out to steal the spotlight for himself!

added.title: Bring on the Bad Guys
added.description: Axel, Zoe, and the team confront Madcap and his minions as they terrorize a local supermarket.

added.title: Spies Like Us
added.description: Uncle Andrew warns Axel that his vintage "Agent Danger" action figure is off-limits, only to have the toy escape on its own! Axel and the team must return Danger to its rightful place before Uncle Andrew finds out.

added.title: Return of Thermometron 9000
added.description: During a brutal heatwave, Axel and his team must track down Thermometron 9000, stolen by Ice Crusher for two purposes - to keep his hockey rink from melting and to bait the good toys into a rematch!

added.title: Just Like Robots
added.description: Axel and the team find themselves bested by Madcap when the baddie uses their digital devices to track their every move in combat, forcing our heroes to act unpredictably.

added.title: The Throw Down/Brawl for It All
added.description: The Throw Down: Lightning reveals his discovery of the Mind Core Cell but the AO arrive only to discover that Magnus has already beaten them to it./Brawl for It All: With both team's Bakugan knocked into a hibernation state by the Mind Core Cell only Dan and Magnus remain locked in a brawl for it all!

added.title: Career Opportunities/Punch the Clock
added.description: Career Opportunities: After defeating Magnus the AO get an offer of employment from a surprising source Philomena Dusk!/Punch the Clock: During a commercial to celebrate their joining the AAAnimus team Dan and the AO rebel before they sellout.

added.title: High Flying Hostiles/Backfire Brawl
added.description: High Flying Hostiles: While escorting the Mind Core Cell to AAAnimus Campus, the AO are attacked by Masato Kazami and his Body Guards./Backfire Brawl: Philomena's attempt to refocus the Mind Core Cell's power backfires and the AO must fight their fellow employees inside the AAAnimus Campus.

added.title: Hostile Take Over/The Big Bounce
added.description: Hostile Take Over: After more unsuccessful attempts to harness Core Cell energy the AO must battle their own Bakugan with AAAnimus tech in order to save them./The Big Bounce: The AO confront Philomena with concerns about her control over the Core Cell energy and are fired in the most unceremonious of manners.

added.title: Awesome vs. AAAnimus
added.description: Awesome V Aaanimus, Part 1: The AO plan on sneaking into AAAnimus and rescuing their Bakugan but are stopped by Benton who offers up an alternate plan./Awesome V Aaanimus, Part 2: The AO team up with Benton Dusk to recapture their stolen Bakugan and free the energy from the Mind Core Cell under the control of AAAnimus.

added.title: Landlord Lord
added.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

added.title: Scary Tales
added.description: During the gang's Halloween party, Unikitty discovers Brick isn't scared of anything! To get him in the holiday spirit, the gang tell their own ideas of what a spooky story is, hoping to scare the emotionless Rick for once, with each tale even scarier (and sillier) than the last!

added.title: Float On
added.description: Unikitty plans a parade to celebrate being unique, with everyone designing their own personalized floats! But Master Frown plans to ruin the parade with a super depressing float! It becomes an intense (and hilariously slow) car-versus-car float duel as Unikitty and the others try and take him down! Will Unikitty pump the brakes on Frown's low-speed scheme?

added.title: Space Mission: Danger
added.description: After their spaceship explodes, Unikitty and the gang float helplessly through space. As they try to formulate a plan that will get them home safe, they flash back to how each of them is responsible for their ship being destroyed. Will they make it home, and more importantly who will be to blame if they don't.

added.title: Top of the Naughty List
added.description: It's Christmas Eve and Brock is excited for Santa to come and visit as he settles down for a bedtime story from Master Frown, Unikitty and gang burst in. They are there to stop Master Frown from ruining any more Christmases. Frown pleads innocent but Unikitty and the gang tell the stories of the past Christmases he has already ruined.  Will Frown prove his innocence or will he rocket to the top of the Naughty List?

added.title: Be a Team
added.description: Mr. Gar brings in some team building experts to help KO, Enid and Rad.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: Point to the Plaza
added.description: When a Gloop infestation takes over the plaza, Point arrives to contain the situation.

added.title: The So-Bad-Ical
added.description: When a new substitute shows up, KO and Dendy decide they need to get their old teacher back.

added.title: Let's Watch the Boxmore Show
added.description: Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.

added.title: Legend of Torbaclaun
added.description: When the Sweetypies think the mythical Torbaclaun has come to Pure Heart Valley, Mao Mao tries to prove to them that it isn't real.

added.title: Meet Tanya Keys
added.description: When bounty hunter Tanya Keys comes to town for Badgerclops, it's up to Mao Mao and Adorabat to save their friend -- even if he's been on the wrong side of the law.

added.title: Weapon of Choice
added.description: Worried that his sword is a glorified consolation prize, Mao Mao sets out to prove the worth of his weapon.

added.title: The Truth Stinks
added.description: Badgerclops smells, but Mao Mao and Adorabat don't know how to tell him.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: When they think each others' lives are easier, the heroes switch roles.

added.title: Goodbye and Good Riddance
added.description: Summer's over and Ben is back at school. Unable to tell anyone that's he all these cool aliens that they've heard about all summer, Ben suddenly realizes he's gone from a "hero" to a "zero", that is until Vilgax comes after him with a vengeance. Ben must now reveal his hero side to his parents and to his fellow classmates. In doing so he saves his town and teams up with his dad to destroy Vilgax once and for all. But there is some bad news...Gwen has switched schools and is in Ben's class!

added.title: Ben 10 vs. Negative 10 Part 1
added.description: Ben, Max Ben and Gwen investigate a couple of daring break-ins, only to discover they were both once secret Plumber installations. What our heroes find out is that those responsible for the break-ins are working for The Forever King. He's brought together a rogue's gallery of some of Ben's most notorious enemies to eventually steal the world's most powerful energy source...located deep inside the Plumber bunker at Mount Rushmore.

added.title: Ben 10 vs. Negative 10 Part 2
added.description: Ben, Max and Gwen put up an Alamo like stand inside the bunker at Mount Rushmore and against great odds take down the Forever King's band of baddies. In the end, Ben goes Upchuck and digests the powerful energy source, preventing the Forever King from using it for nefarious purposes. However this ultimate baddie is able to disappear...perhaps to return once again.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 1
added.description: After a heated argument, Ben and Rook go their separate ways, giving Khyber the Huntsman his best chance to capture Ben! (Introducing Dr. Psychobos, new Nemetrix aliens Mucillator & Terroranchula; new Ben alien Ballweevil.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: The Return of Aunt Grandma
added.description: Aunt Grandma is back and still bent on ruining Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Messy Bessy
added.description: Seth must clean his room and learn to be a neater person in order to keep Messy Bessy from making his life a nightmare.

added.title: Memory Foam
added.description: When a new mattress sucks away all of Pizza Steve's memories, Uncle Grandpa and the crew must find a way to get them back.

added.title: Fleas Help Me
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang help their K9 pal, Charlie Burgers, get rid of his flea infestation.

added.title: Wicked Shades
added.description: When Pizza Steve borrows Uncle Grandpa's sunglasses, he sees things in a whole new light.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: El Elegido
added.description: Tobías intenta ser el mejor amigo de Gumball.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Fe
added.description: Alan perdió su fe en la humanidad y puso el mundo blanco y negro. Gumball tiene que superar el odio que siente hacia Alan para recuperar el color a través del canto.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Leccion
added.description: Gumball y Darwin se hacen cargo de los trabajos de Larry durante 5 minutos y se dan cuenta de lo desagradable que son.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Amiga
added.description: Anaís y Jamie forjan una extraña amistad cuando se las acusa de un crimen que no cometieron.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Amo
added.description: Los Watterson juegan un juego de rol fantástico para resolver sus diferencias.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Pleito animado
added.description: Control Fenómeno obliga a los Titanes y a la Scooby-pandilla a competir en Pleito Familiar.

added.title: Trabajando en Equipo
added.description: El Sr. Gar trae a un equipo de expertos en construcción para que ayuden a K.O., Enid y Rad.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Mi Bella Carol
added.description: K.O., Enid y Rad se unen para ayudar a Carol para una ocasión especial.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Veamos el Show de Boxmore
added.description: Nuestros héroes descubren que las grabaciones de la cámara de seguridad de Boxmore son la cosa más divertida del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Mal Radical
added.description: Cuando llega un nuevo reemplazo, K.O. y Dendy deciden que necesitan recuperar a su antiguo profesor.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Apointa a la Plaza
added.description: Cuando la plaza se infesta de pegote, P.O.I.N.T. llega para contener la situación.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Los Supervillanso se Unen
added.description: Después de una pausa en las payasadas alienígenas, un inquieto Ben les sugiere a Max y Gwen que podría ser un mejor héroe si fuera solo. Pero cuando Vilgax consigue la ayuda de Zombozo para construir un mecanismo hipnotizador gigante para hipnotizar al mundo entero, Ben debe replantearse su estrategia si quiere derrotar al equipo de supervillanos.

added.title: Puedo Quedarmelo?
added.description: Tras toparse con una adorable criatura, híbrido de gato, perro y conejo, Ben no hace caso al consejo del abuelo Max y se lleva al animal a escondidas al Chatarra. Pero pronto empiezan los problemas porque ila creación del Dr. Animal lo delata!

added.title: Nuggets de Pollo de Sabiduria
added.description: Cuando Ben y Max comienzan a discutir, Ben se convierte en Fuego para desahogarse, contra la voluntad de Max. Pero una vez que el Dr. Animo lo ve y convierte a Max en un pollo, Ben debe enmendar su error si quiere salvar a su Abuelo y detener al Dr. Animo.

added.title: Todo Enrollado
added.description: Cuando Ben se impacienta con el ritmo lento de la jardinería, se convierte en O-E Overflow para acelerar las cosas y, por accidente, inunda el jardín de la comunidad.

added.title: Rey Koil
added.description: Ben y Gwen pasan el día como voluntarios en Repto Ranch y se enfrentan cara a cara con el Rey Koil. Pero necesitan superar rápidamente su miedo a las serpientes si quieren rescatar a las criaturas liberadas y derrotar al serpenteante villano.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: Azulejo
added.description: Steven cuestiona los motivos de una misteriosa fusión que de repente se presenta en su casa.

added.title: El futuro es de Carton
added.description: Los niños conocen a un excéntrico Creador de Cartón que invita a Craig a ayudarlo a terminar su obra maestra.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Camada
added.description: La determinación de Craig de conseguirle a su abuelo un caparazón de cigarra hace que él, Kelsey y JP queden atrapados en su tronco.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Bajo el Puente
added.description: Craig y sus amigos viajan para encontrar madreselva en el arroyo, pero descubren una parte completamente nueva del arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: #NoDerribenElArbol
added.description: Jessica Cruz y Pam Isley se unen para evitar que un antiguo árbol sea talado, pero ninguna se da cuenta de quien es el alter ego de la otra ni los extremos a los que llegarán para proteger lo que es importante.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: El Reino del Jamas
added.description: Los ninja llegan al Never-Realm donde rápidamente se sienten abrumados. Afortunadamente, son recibidos por una tribu de pescadores de hielo que les dicen que Zane ha sido encarcelado por el malvado Emperador de hielo.

added.title: #IlusionesDeGrandeza
added.description: Lista para salir de la sombra de su padre, Zatara busca la fama y el reconocimiento con una presentación para su propia audiencia en el muelle. Pero cuando su acto es tildado de fraude, ella pierde el control y accidentalmente libera terribles seres que causan estragos en el muelle.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: El Hacedor de Fuego
added.description: El Emperador de Hielo se entera de la llegada de los ninjas y envía a sus guerreros Samurais Blizzard a destruirlos, y a todos los aldeanos que los albergaron.

added.title: La Invitacion
added.description: Craig y sus amigos están invitados a una exclusiva merienda con deliciosos postres, si es que pueden quedarse hasta el final de la fiesta.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: #ElShowDeLasBestias
added.description: Cuando Babs y Kara discuten sobre cual de sus perros es mejor, deciden resolver la situación en el concurso anual de perros de Metrópolis, donde Ace, el Bati-sabueso y Krypto, el Superperro, deberán salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: La Leyenda del Torbaclaun
added.description: Cuando los Corazoncitos creen que el mítico Torbaclaun ha llegado al Valle Puro Corazón, Mao Mao intenta demostrarles que no es real.

added.title: Un Aliado Peculiar
added.description: Lloyd se enfrenta a los Samurais Blizzard del Emperador de Hielo, pero es rescatado por un lobo extraño con quien desarrolla una amistad peculiar.

added.title: Nido de buitres
added.description: Craig y sus amigos forman una banda, pero a Craig lo atormenta una pesadilla aterradora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Peor Ninja de Todos
added.description: De regreso en ciudad Ninjago, tres criminales se enteran de la ausencia de los ninjas y organizan una fuga de la prisión Kryptarium, contando historias sobre cómo fueron capturados mientras avanzaban.

added.title: Conozcan a Tanya Keys
added.description: Cuando Tanya Keys, la cazadora de recompensas, llega a la ciudad para atrapar a Colosal, Mao Mao y Adorabat son los encargados de salvar a su amigo... aunque se haya metido en asuntos ilegales.

added.title: #LaConvencionDeGotham
added.description: Un divertido día para Barbara Gordon y su mejor amiga Harley Quinzel en la Convención Anual de Gotham City, es puesto cabeza abajo cuando, de la nada, ila malvada Harley Quinn aparece para sembrar el caos! Por suerte para todos, Batgirl se encuentra casualmente en el área...
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: El Mensaje
added.description: Lloyd y su compañero lobo encuentran una cueva y encuentran al Mech adentro. Escuchan un mensaje de Zane que les da una pista de su destino.

added.title: Arma de Eleccion
added.description: Preocupado de que su espada sea un premio consuelo con pretensiones, Mao Mao decide salir a demostrar el valor de su arma.

added.title: La Verdad Apesta
added.description: Colosal huele mal, pero Mao Mao y Adorabat no saben cómo decírselo.

added.title: Dia de Intercambio
added.description: Cuando los héroes creen que la vida del otro es más sencilla, intercambian sus papeles.

added.title: #AbracadabraPalooza
added.description: En un intento por hacer que Karen se sienta mejor con un granito que le salió, Zee le cuenta la avergonzante transición que le dio poderes mágicos y la grieta que eso generó entre ella y su padre.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Senor Casero
added.description: El propietario amenazó a Master Frown y a Brock con desalojarlos a menos que arreglen el daño que le hicieron a su apartamento. Preocupado, Brock invita a Unikitty y a la pandilla para que los ayuden. En lugar de hacer lo que los chicos quieren en su casa, Unikitty procede a hacer lo que ella quiere. Al darse cuenta de su error, devuelve el apartamento a su antiguo estado asqueroso, pero ahora Frown y Brock están en peligro de desalojo de nuevo. Deben aliarse a Unikitty y la banda para luchar contra el malvado casero y salvar su hogar.

added.title: Historias de miedo
added.description: Durante la fiesta de Halloween de la banda, iUnikitty descubre que Rick no le teme a nada! Para contagiarle el espíritu festivo, Unikitty cuenta sus propias ideas de lo que es una historia espeluznante, con la esperanza de asustar al inconmovible de Rick por una vez. iPero cada cuento es aún más espeluznante (y más tonto) que el anterior!

added.title: El Desfile
added.description: Unikitty planea un desfile para celebrar lo que cada uno tiene de único, idonde cada uno diseñará sus propias carrozas personalizadas! Pero Master Frown planea arruinar el desfile con una carroza súper deprimente. El desfile se convierte en un duelo intenso (y de una lentitud divertidísima) de coche contra carroza mientras Unikitty y los demás intentan derribar a Master Frown! ¿Le pondrá un freno Unikitty al complot a baja velocidad de Frown?

added.title: Mision Espacial Peligrosa
added.description: Después de la explosión de su nave espacial, Unikitty y la banda flotan indefensos por el espacio. Mientras tratan de formular un plan que los lleve a casa a salvo, vuelven a ver qué parte de la responsabilidad por la destrucción de su nave tiene cada uno. ¿Lograrán volver a casa? Y lo que es más importante, ¿quién tendrá la culpa si no lo hacen?

added.title: Lista de Traviesos
added.description: Es Nochebuena y Brock está emocionado por la visita de Santa Claus. Mientras se prepara para que Master Frown le lea un cuento para dormir, Unikitty y la banda irrumpen en su casa. Están ahí para evitar que Master Frown arruine más Navidades. Frown se declara inocente, pero Unikitty y la banda cuentan las historias de las Navidades pasadas que ya arruinó. ¿Frown probará su inocencia o se pondrá a la cabeza de la lista de los traviesos?

added.title: Que Vengan Los Chicos Malos
added.description: Axel, Zoe y el equipo se enfrentan a Madcap y sus secuaces mientras aterrorizan a un supermercado local.

added.title: Espias Como Nosotros
added.description: El tío Andrew le advierte a Axel que su figura de acción "Agente Peligro" está prohibida, isolo para que el juguete escape solo! Axel y el equipo deben devolver a Danger al lugar que le corresponde antes de que el tío Andrew se entere.

added.title: El regreso de Thermometron 9000
added.description: Durante una ola de calor brutal, Axel y su equipo deben rastrear Thermometron 9000, robado por Ice Crusher para dos propósitos: ievitar que su pista de hockey se derrita y cebar los buenos juguetes en una revancha!

added.title: Como Robots
added.description: Axel y el equipo se ven superados por Madcap cuando el malo usa sus dispositivos digitales para rastrear cada uno de sus movimientos en combate, lo que obliga a nuestros héroes a actuar de manera impredecible.

added.title: Un Gran Enfrentamiento
added.description: Lightning por fin revela la ubicación de la Célula Núcleo, pero cuando Los Fantásticos llegan, descubren que Magnus fue más rápido que ellos.

added.title: Ego - Egoista
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla tienen que demostrar que no son egoístas cuando hacen sus buenas acciones.

added.title: Salchichas y Dulce Golpe
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben superar sus obsesiones por las salchichas y los videojuegos.

added.title: La Formula de Manzana
added.description: Manzana necesita encontrar una fórmula divertida que le permita conseguir un papel cómico en una película.

added.title: Perdiendo el Control
added.description: Después de más intentos fallidos por aprovechar la energía la Célula núcleo, Los Fantásticos deben pelear contra sus propios Bakugan usando tecnología AAAnimus para salvarlos.

added.title: Despedidos
added.description: Los Fantásticos confrontan a Filomena, preocupados de que ella controle la energía de la Célula núcleo, y son despedidos de una forma poco profesional.

added.title: Un Experimento Fallido
added.description: El plan de Filomena Dusk para redireccionar la energía de la Célula Núcleo fracasa, y Los Fantásticos deben pelear contra sus propios compañeros de trabajo dentro de las instalaciones de AAAnimus.

added.title: Fantasticos vs. AAAnimus Parte 2
added.description: Los Fantásticos unen fuerzas con Benton Dusk para rescatar a sus Bakugan y liberar la energía de la Célula Núcleo que AAAnimus tiene bajo su control.

added.title: Rio de Oro
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla intentan terminar un cuento antes de que el libro desaparezca para siempre.

added.title: La Batalla Decisiva
added.description: Luego de que la Célula Núcleo pusiera en estado de hibernación a los Bakugan de ambos equipos, Dan y Magnus se encuentran atrapados en una batalla donde lo apostarán todo.

added.title: Enemigos en el Aire
added.description: Cuando Los Fantásticos transportan la Célula Núcleo a las instalaciones de AAAnimus, son atacados por Masato Kazami y sus Guardaespaldas.

added.title: Oportunidades Laborales
added.description: Después de derrotar a Magnus, los Fantásticos reciben una oferta de empleo de alguien inesperado... Filomena Dusk.

added.title: Fantasticos vs. AAAnimus Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos planean infiltrarse a AAAnimus para rescatar a sus Bakugan, pero Benton los detiene para ofrecerles un plan alternativo.

added.title: Un Nuevo Empleo
added.description: Durante un comercial para celebrar su contrato con el equipo AAAnimus, Dan y Los Fantásticos deciden rebelarse antes que traicionar sus principios.

added.title: Sigue Tus Suenos
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín necesitan encontrar un sueño que perseguir para que sus vidas tengan un rumbo.
